
###############
# PCB Locator #
###############

** Usage:

- Put the .py in the directory of gimp/plug-ins/
- Add execution permissions.
- In one image, Create 2 layers that represents the top & bottom view(usually the size of the cupper plate)
- Both needs the same name and "top" and "bottom" for each.
- Add all the boards as independent layers, event for bottom and top(the name for bottom and top again, the same with top and bottom)
- Place all the bottom sides in the proper position of the bottom view.
- Execute the script, PCB-> PCB Locator
- In the text field, type: bottomview(bottomboard1,bottomboard2,bottomboard3, etc...)
- All the top boards will be placed in to the topview layer, in the proper position(mirror, and translation).

